    "intro": "Interpretation asks what 2 Samuel 11 means in its canonical, historical, and theological context — moving from the narrative's surface to the author's intent and the text's place in the larger story of the Davidic covenant. The movements below trace the chapter's argument from the initial dereliction through the divine verdict, with attention to the chapter's role in the book as a whole and its theological weight within the canon.",
